1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,729
[Previously]
Ai Mor.

2
00:00:01,730 --> 00:00:05,519
For scars on the chest... What do you think they could be caused by?

3
00:00:05,519 --> 00:00:09,460
Don't you feel like he reminds you of someone?

4
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,720
Like Nong Torfun?

5
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:15,970
The two of them...were they...

6
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:19,160
If they were a couple?

7
00:00:21,060 --> 00:00:22,693
For me...

8
00:00:23,430 --> 00:00:29,090
Torfun is like the little sister that I love the most... Forever.

9
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:35,089
[Seven months earlier]

10
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:36,289
Sure, Hia.

11
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:38,470
But you've cleared the road for sure, right?

12
00:00:39,230 --> 00:00:42,640
Yes. If that's what you're saying, Hia, then I feel at ease.

13
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:45,939
Go ahead and handle it, Hia. Thank you so much.

14
00:00:45,940 --> 00:00:48,119
Hey, I'm going to go get my car first. See you on the road.

15
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:49,749
- See you.
- See you.

16
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:51,620
Of course. Of course.

17
00:01:06,260 --> 00:01:07,649
Yes, Hia.

18
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:09,419
Hey! Hia, just a moment, alright?

19
00:01:09,420 --> 00:01:10,739
Hey, Dude.

20
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:12,520
Tian, are you alright?

21
00:01:19,930 --> 00:01:22,709
Hey, I'm alright. Just a bit lightheaded.

22
00:01:22,709 --> 00:01:25,900
I think... you really shouldn't, Dude.

23
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:28,820
Your condition seems a bit strange.

24
00:01:38,850 --> 00:01:40,209
Why, Dude?

25
00:01:40,210 --> 00:01:41,999
Are you afraid that I'll die?

26
00:01:41,999 --> 00:01:44,650
What kind of shit are you saying?

27
00:01:44,650 --> 00:01:49,330
Hey, come on. Have a little faith in my baby.

28
00:01:49,330 --> 00:01:51,909
I spent so much time building this car.

29
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:53,709
You don't need to worry, alright?

30
00:01:53,709 --> 00:01:55,443
Come on, let's go.

31
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:13,983
Hey, Ai Tian!

32
00:02:13,983 --> 00:02:15,719
I don't think this is going to work anymore.

33
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:18,550
Just cancel it. Trust me.

34
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:25,519
If I back out I'd be a chicken then, right?

35
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:28,463
Nong Tian.

36
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,833
Nong Tian.

37
00:02:31,890 --> 00:02:33,523
Nong Tian!

38
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,209
- Yes, Phi?
- Let's go.

39
00:02:36,209 --> 00:02:37,479
Did you want to try driving for a bit?

40
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:42,199
So you can brag to your friends that you have driven through a series of downhill curves.

41
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:46,469
It's probably better if I don't, Phi. I don't know how to drive.

42
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:49,859
Oh, okay! Then go ahead and get in the car.

43
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,293
- Let's go.
- Alright.

44
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:54,149
Be good for your dad today, alright?

45
00:02:54,149 --> 00:02:56,140
You can't die on me, alright?

46
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,849
Let's go! Can you get up alright?

47
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:00,383
Yes, I can.

48
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:07,770
[Pha Pun Dao School]

49
00:03:45,490 --> 00:03:50,089
When Ai Phu first said it to me, I really didn't think it.

50
00:03:50,089 --> 00:03:52,160
But it really is similar.

51
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:55,370
What's similar, P' Mor?

52
00:03:56,510 --> 00:03:59,810
Nong Tian, you really do do a lot of things just like Nong Torfun.

53
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:04,330
That person, whenever she sat in my car, she also liked to do that too.

54
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:17,200
Chief Phu thinks that I remind him of Khru Torfun?

55
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:27,040
What's your relation to Torfun?

56
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:34,049
Why are you asking me something like that?

57
00:04:34,049 --> 00:04:38,460
I saw Torfun's badge in your possession.

58
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:46,139
I found it when I moved into the house.

59
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:49,830
I guess Khru Torfun might have forgotten it there.

60
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:52,329
Chief, did you want it?

61
00:04:52,329 --> 00:04:54,480
I'll bring it to you later.

62
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,133
Chief?

63
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:13,110
I'm sorry about her.

64
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:05,710
♫ The story that's been told however many times is still the same ♫

65
00:06:05,710 --> 00:06:12,190
♫ It's that I love you, love you. It has never changed ♫

66
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:18,660
♫ If perhaps the stars hear the words of the prayers within my heart ♫

67
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:29,960
♫ No matter how many thousands of times, I'll still ask for my heart to be near you ♫

68
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:33,860
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

69
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:40,560
[Chapter 5]

70
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,350
[22 Bangkok]

71
00:06:53,210 --> 00:06:54,849
- Nong Tian.
- Yes?

72
00:06:54,849 --> 00:06:56,809
This is Chiang Mai, alright?

73
00:06:56,810 --> 00:06:59,349
It's not Bangkok. Are you sure you're alright?

74
00:06:59,349 --> 00:07:02,429
Here, Phi. It's Google Maps. No need to worry.

75
00:07:02,429 --> 00:07:04,769
Alright, alright, alright.

76
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:07,779
Then I'll go run my errands, alright? Whenever you're done just call me, alright?

77
00:07:07,779 --> 00:07:09,200
- Got it, Phi.
- Okay.

78
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,070
- See you later.
- Yes!

79
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:30,569
- Hello, dude.
- Damn, Tian! I thought you were dead already!

80
00:07:30,569 --> 00:07:31,979
Not yet, man!

81
00:07:31,979 --> 00:07:34,649
I'd kept trying to call you to the point that I was about to just quit calling already!

82
00:07:34,649 --> 00:07:38,719
Yeah, sorry, Dude. There's barely any damn signal up there.

83
00:07:38,719 --> 00:07:42,019
- Where on earth are you, Dude?
- Chiang Mai.

84
00:07:42,019 --> 00:07:43,739
For real?

85
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:46,819
When you sent me a Line message about you becoming a teacher,
[T/N: An social media app used for texting and voice/video calls]

86
00:07:46,819 --> 00:07:49,169
I thought you were kidding.

87
00:07:49,169 --> 00:07:51,499
But, Dude... When the heck are you coming back?

88
00:07:51,499 --> 00:07:53,479
Do you want me to pick you up?

89
00:07:53,479 --> 00:07:54,979
Not yet.

90
00:07:54,979 --> 00:07:57,889
I just came to do some errands in the city.

91
00:07:57,889 --> 00:07:59,429
Oh, right, Tian!

92
00:07:59,429 --> 00:08:01,289
Wait for me right there. I'm going to go see you friend!

93
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:02,489
Huh?

94
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:04,199
Hey! Ai Tul!

95
00:08:04,199 --> 00:08:05,633
Hello?

96
00:08:06,470 --> 00:08:08,200
Hello?

97
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:36,210
[Materials: 1. Bamboo stick, 2. Paper, 3. Rope]

98
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,610
[Phaphirun Unit]

99
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:53,659
I want the village health volunteers to do site visits here more often.

100
00:08:53,660 --> 00:08:56,779
Oh! Whenever they come, we always get delicious food!

101
00:08:56,779 --> 00:09:00,659
Chang. Chang go bring some food to Khru Tian later, alright?

102
00:09:00,659 --> 00:09:03,089
That's probably not necessary, Chief.

103
00:09:03,090 --> 00:09:04,509
Why?

104
00:09:04,509 --> 00:09:06,750
Khru isn't there, sir.

105
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,413
Where did he go?

106
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:11,479
He went into the city.

107
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,430
What did he go there for?

108
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:17,369
I don't know.

109
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:19,320
Who did he go with?

110
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:21,979
I don't know.

111
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:23,913
Who allowed him?

112
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:26,309
Uh... I don't know.

113
00:09:26,310 --> 00:09:29,870
When he's back, I'll ask him for you, alright?

114
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:33,470
- No need.
- Guess I just don't need to eat!

115
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:40,370
Osmanthus fragrant tea!

116
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:42,529
Osmanthus fragrant tea, dears!

117
00:09:42,529 --> 00:09:44,859
Loong! What are you selling?

118
00:09:44,859 --> 00:09:47,410
Fragrant tea. It's fragrant tea.

119
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:50,410
How much is a sachet?

120
00:09:50,410 --> 00:09:52,259
This bag is 80 baht.

121
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:53,839
Oh... Can this be kept for a long time?

122
00:09:53,839 --> 00:09:56,259
It can be kept up to a year.

123
00:09:56,260 --> 00:09:57,829
In that case, I'll help buy a sachet from you then.

124
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:59,989
Ah, thank you. Thank you.

125
00:09:59,989 --> 00:10:01,599
Here take this, alright? I've already put the money, alright?

126
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:04,410
Alright. Thank you.

127
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:09,839
Loong, how much is a small sachet?

128
00:10:09,839 --> 00:10:13,070
Oh, this sachet is 40 baht, son.

129
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:25,430
Then...I'll take two sachets.

130
00:10:26,950 --> 00:10:28,309
Thank you so much.

131
00:10:28,309 --> 00:10:29,819
This is a 100 baht.

132
00:10:29,819 --> 00:10:31,629
Uh... For the change, should I grab it myself?

133
00:10:31,629 --> 00:10:33,830
Ah, sure, sure. Go ahead and grab it.

134
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:37,970
Thank you so much. Thank you.

135
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:53,749
Hey, seriously let me ask you... When you're up there, you're eating local foods.

136
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:56,750
You're coming down here and still eating it again. Aren't you tired of it?

137
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:59,180
My mouth has gotten familiar with it, Phi.

138
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,600
And have you gotten familiar with a person too?

139
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,579
P' Mor, what do you mean?

140
00:11:05,580 --> 00:11:08,090
Well...I mean my friend of course.

141
00:11:12,090 --> 00:11:13,859
I just saw that you guys seemed close is all.

142
00:11:13,859 --> 00:11:16,810
I'm just asking for fun. It's nothing serious.

143
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,640
P' Mor, you and your friend aren't alike at all.

144
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:26,579
That person has no sense of humor.

145
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:29,869
That's how he is. He's a tiger that rarely smiles.

146
00:11:29,869 --> 00:11:32,070
But in actuality, he's pretty sweet though.

147
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:34,159
That's not true, Phi!

148
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:37,169
If he really was sweet, then he would've had a lover by now!

149
00:11:37,169 --> 00:11:40,779
Oh, what's this? Even though he didn't come with us,

150
00:11:40,779 --> 00:11:42,930
there's still someone complaining about him.

151
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:49,940
Hey, let me seriously ask you... Do you mind poor state officers?

152
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:52,800
I've never judged people based on their occupations anyway, Phi.

153
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:59,760
That means...that a young officer around here has a chance then.

154
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:12,989
Give me your Facebook.

155
00:12:12,990 --> 00:12:16,140
In case when you go back, Nong Tian, I'll be able to contact you.

156
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:24,059
Hey! I totally forgot, Phi.

157
00:12:24,059 --> 00:12:27,560
Before I came here, I already deactivated my Facebook.

158
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:31,999
Oh, that's pretty strange then.

159
00:12:31,999 --> 00:12:34,550
I don't often see someone who doesn't use Facebook at all.

160
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:40,939
Oh, right! Ai Phu was telling me that you had surgery.

161
00:12:40,939 --> 00:12:42,840
What surgery did you have?

162
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:46,759
For heart disease, Phi.

163
00:12:46,759 --> 00:12:50,700
But you don't need to worry, P' Mor. I'm totally okay now.

164
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,899
- You have to take care of yourself, alright?
- Sure.

165
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:08,873
P' Mor?

166
00:13:08,873 --> 00:13:10,860
Who's that at the table over there, Phi?

167
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:17,980
That man in the patterned shirt is Por Liang Sakda.
[T/N: Por Liang literally means stepdad, but also refers to a very powerful, wealthy and influential man. Similar to a godfather.]

168
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:20,689
The other guy is his henchman.

169
00:13:20,690 --> 00:13:22,123
Why?

170
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:27,330
Because those guys were the merchants who were buying tea from the villagers, Phi.

171
00:13:28,530 --> 00:13:31,330
The ones that I had a fight with last week.

172
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:38,619
These guys...they're pretty influential around here.

173
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:41,639
His connections and networks are pretty good.

174
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:43,760
No one wants to offend him.

175
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:48,120
But most of them know that these guys...they're involved in grey (illegal) business.

176
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:50,639
He donates to the forestry department,

177
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:53,589
but is involved in the illegal wildlife trade.

178
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:54,620
Very contradicting.

179
00:13:56,740 --> 00:14:01,470
Like those who'll plant a forest, but have elephant ivory in their home, Phi?

180
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:05,499
You have quite a sharp tongue there.

181
00:14:05,499 --> 00:14:08,350
It's no wonder why trouble always finds you.

182
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,749
Who would dare to go against him?

183
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:18,390
Phu's own unit...it's also supported by Por Liang too.

184
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:23,019
Doing good to erase what's evil.

185
00:14:23,019 --> 00:14:25,120
That can't be though, right, Phi?

186
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:29,640
Phu himself also isn't really happy about it either.

187
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:32,370
But he can't say anything.

188
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:36,120
I understand, Phi.

189
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:40,760
I probably really am a damn trouble magnet.

190
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:45,069
Sorry, Phi.

191
00:14:45,070 --> 00:14:46,499
That's alright, that's alright.

192
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,719
But...just try not to look for trouble with him.

193
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:50,719
If you can avoid him, just avoid him.

194
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,153
Alright?

195
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,490
Miss?

196
00:14:58,490 --> 00:14:59,669
The bill, please.

197
00:14:59,669 --> 00:15:02,520
There was someone who already paid it for you.

198
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,423
- Full!
- Full!

199
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:26,939
I'm so full, Phi.

200
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:28,439
Is there anything else you want to go eat next?

201
00:15:28,439 --> 00:15:30,390
How about dessert then?

202
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:39,679
Thank you for this meal, Por Liang Sakda.

203
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,489
Thank you, sir. You shouldn't have.

204
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,249
It's no problem.

205
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:47,179
This restaurant is well...owned by an acquaintance of mine.

206
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:49,699
Doctor, you go to take care of the people of Pha Pun Dao.

207
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:52,719
It's like you're taking care of the people for me too.

208
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,850
This is just a small matter.

209
00:15:54,850 --> 00:15:56,009
Yes, sir.

210
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:59,909
If you're missing anything, you can just go ahead and let your boss know, Doctor.

211
00:15:59,909 --> 00:16:02,300
Consider it as trying to help each other out.

212
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:04,113
Of course, sir.

213
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:14,929
This... His name is Khru Tian, sir.

214
00:16:14,929 --> 00:16:18,489
He's the new teacher up in the hills.

215
00:16:18,489 --> 00:16:20,059
Good.

216
00:16:20,059 --> 00:16:25,830
A young man, someone of the younger generation, with compassion to help others.

217
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:28,599
But it can be a bit difficult up there.

218
00:16:28,599 --> 00:16:34,180
I hope you're able to adjust yourself, Khru, to match with the villagers who've been there before you, alright?

219
00:16:35,690 --> 00:16:37,690
I'm trying.

220
00:16:39,450 --> 00:16:42,200
I'd like to thank you, Khru, on behalf of the villagers as well.

221
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:55,780
Someone like you, Khru...is hard to find.

222
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:58,590
You should stay around for a long time, alright?

223
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,799
I'll get going first then, Doctor.

224
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:07,330
Yes, sir. Goodbye.

225
00:17:23,439 --> 00:17:24,909
Hello, Ai Tul?

226
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:26,119
Huh?

227
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:27,829
Dude, you've already arrived in Chiang Mai?

228
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:31,640
Oh...yeah, yeah. Alright, alright. See you.

229
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,833
P' Mor?

230
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:41,780
For today... could I not go back to Pha Pun Dao yet?

231
00:17:45,290 --> 00:17:49,100
[The Loft Café]

232
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:53,949
Hey! Ai Tul!

233
00:17:53,950 --> 00:17:55,483
Ai Tian!

234
00:17:56,480 --> 00:18:00,760
Hey! How've you been, dude? Give me a hug.

235
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:05,269
I can't believe that you'd come to see me!

236
00:18:05,269 --> 00:18:07,580
I told you, I'm a man of my word!

237
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:11,690
Ai Tul, you shit. I missed you, Dude.

238
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:13,819
-Hey, are those your words your opinion, Dude?
- Yeah.

239
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:15,209
Alright then.

240
00:18:15,209 --> 00:18:17,260
Ai Tian, you ass.

241
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,889
If it's like that... That must mean that you also missed me then.

242
00:18:21,890 --> 00:18:24,330
Of course, my dear friend.

243
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:29,380
And, Dude... what the heck are you wearing?

244
00:18:29,380 --> 00:18:30,519
Why?

245
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:33,699
Would you have another one for me? That way I can just change into it!

246
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,193
Here.

247
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:43,039
To my best friend, who has fulfilled his wish of being a teacher on a hill.

248
00:18:46,670 --> 00:18:48,609
Ha! You're confused, right, Dude?

249
00:18:48,609 --> 00:18:50,970
They say that if you drink it, it's good for your body's health.

250
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:53,960
[V Boost]

251
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:57,430
[V Boost]

252
00:19:12,230 --> 00:19:14,480
It really is good for the body's health, dude.

253
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:17,140
What the heck is with you?

254
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,373
Nothing.

255
00:19:30,890 --> 00:19:32,439
Oh, right, Dude.

256
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:35,480
And...did my mom ever call you worrying about me?

257
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:38,293
Let me count real quick.

258
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,939
Just once, Dude!

259
00:19:41,939 --> 00:19:43,449
Why did you even bother counting, Dude?

260
00:19:43,450 --> 00:19:45,979
Yeah, but I didn't tell her anything!

261
00:19:45,979 --> 00:19:47,579
Your mom, she just hung up.

262
00:19:47,579 --> 00:19:50,429
Well, at first...I thought that your mom would grill me more.

263
00:19:50,429 --> 00:19:54,609
Yeah...that's good then. You better not tell her anything.

264
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:57,729
So when I get back, I can just get an earful once.

265
00:19:57,729 --> 00:20:01,490
Sure. And what about you? How have you been?

266
00:20:01,490 --> 00:20:02,829
Me?

267
00:20:02,829 --> 00:20:05,080
Absolutely amazing, Dude.

268
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,259
Dude, just imagine it.

269
00:20:06,260 --> 00:20:09,479
On a day when the power at your house goes out... Damn, it's as quiet as that.

270
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:13,309
Like... Once the sun goes down, it's like that every single day.

271
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:15,859
And did you know? The first day when I arrived,

272
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:17,369
I couldn't eat anything at all.

273
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:19,909
So I had to just force myself to eat, Dude.

274
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:22,699
And you know? I've just become friends with mosquitoes!

275
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:24,769
I get bitten by them every day!

276
00:20:24,770 --> 00:20:28,249
And like, there was one day where I...was hurting...

277
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:30,480
hurting to take a dump.

278
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:32,319
I was hurting so bad!

279
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:34,739
So I held a lantern from the house and went to the toilet

280
00:20:34,739 --> 00:20:37,879
But, damn, the toilet and the house are like 30 meters apart, Dude.

281
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:40,899
The path was so damn dark too. I was just walking and holding as I went.

282
00:20:40,899 --> 00:20:42,759
Once I put it down,

283
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:45,519
That was it. I was in the middle of letting it out...

284
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:48,929
And once I looked up at the ceiling, Dude... I was facing a tokay gecko, right?

285
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,879
Dude, think about it. A tokay gecko! Shit, man!
[T/N: Tokay Gecko is a large gecko that constantly makes a "tokay" sound. People are terrified of them and their bite.]

286
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:57,329
So I was like, "Alright..." I quickly pulled my pants, grabbed the lantern, and ran right out.

287
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,100
What are you smiling at?

288
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:05,810
I'm just thinking that...

289
00:21:05,810 --> 00:21:09,130
If it's that difficult, then just why are you staying?

290
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,099
It's just...

291
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,310
It's also good, Dude.

292
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:18,543
Like...

293
00:21:18,543 --> 00:21:21,540
We probably won't come across something like this in our actual lives.

294
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:26,510
So...what's it for then?

295
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:38,083
Well...

296
00:21:39,290 --> 00:21:41,290
I think...

297
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:47,169
I probably wanted to find something new to experience in my life.

298
00:21:47,170 --> 00:21:48,329
That can't be true.

299
00:21:48,330 --> 00:21:52,029
A guy like you, Dude... If you were thinking of doing something new in your life,

300
00:21:52,029 --> 00:21:54,569
by now you would've gone back home a long time ago, Ai Tian!

301
00:21:54,569 --> 00:21:56,839
There must be something more to that.

302
00:21:56,839 --> 00:21:58,479
You better say it.

303
00:21:58,479 --> 00:22:00,113
Right now.

304
00:22:01,270 --> 00:22:02,759
I said, "Say it."

305
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:04,989
Hey, it hurts!

306
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:07,030
Hurry up. Say it.

307
00:22:14,770 --> 00:22:16,203
Chief!

308
00:22:17,260 --> 00:22:18,489
Chief, are you here to see Khru Tian?

309
00:22:18,490 --> 00:22:20,759
That's right. Uh... not at all.

310
00:22:20,759 --> 00:22:23,670
The vendor at the market asked me to bring food to Khru Tian.

311
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,800
- Hello.
- Hello.

312
00:22:34,810 --> 00:22:36,930
- Ai Rang, Ai Rang.
-What?

313
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,229
Chief!

314
00:22:39,230 --> 00:22:42,050
Did you come to wait for Khru Tian all the way at his house?

315
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:44,683
No!

316
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:51,329
That must mean that the Chief probably has something really important.

317
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:53,100
Yeah, that's right.

318
00:22:54,660 --> 00:22:56,659
Help him.

319
00:22:56,659 --> 00:22:58,910
Should... Should I help?

320
00:23:02,630 --> 00:23:04,263
What's the rush?

321
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,469
You're not drinking alcohol either.

322
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:17,349
You've changed just as I said, right?

323
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:18,739
Even though you complained how you're struggling,

324
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:21,290
