325
00:23:22,810 --> 00:23:24,179
Well, I'm actually happy, Dude.

326
00:23:24,179 --> 00:23:26,489
The people there are so damn sweet.

327
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:29,109
Are you going to move houses and just stay here then?

328
00:23:29,110 --> 00:23:32,440
A house? You never know.

329
00:23:33,260 --> 00:23:35,649
Ai Tian, Let me tell you.

330
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:37,639
This isn't your real life, Dude.

331
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,500
How the hell is it not real?

332
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:42,159
Well, if you wanted to just test your life

333
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:45,979
on just how difficult it can be just to take a picture to upload on Facebook,

334
00:23:45,979 --> 00:23:48,129
I could understand that.

335
00:23:48,130 --> 00:23:50,359
But if it's your actual life, Dude,

336
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:55,299
could you really life without having electricity... not having a phone, not having internet?

337
00:23:55,299 --> 00:23:57,039
With your life just continually looping like that.

338
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:59,469
Would you really be able to do that?

339
00:23:59,470 --> 00:24:02,419
But other people are also able live their lives like that.

340
00:24:02,419 --> 00:24:03,649
Dude.

341
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:08,059
Dude, don't you think that if they could choose, would they really want to have that kind of life?

342
00:24:08,059 --> 00:24:10,910
Everyone wants to have a comfortable life.

343
00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:14,359
But there are also people who choose to live their lives like that for real though.

344
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:15,669
Who?

345
00:24:15,670 --> 00:24:18,329
Well...people with a purpose in life.

346
00:24:18,330 --> 00:24:21,669
People who are willing to sacrifice themselves for the sake of others.

347
00:24:21,670 --> 00:24:23,259
Like damn, that's freaking cool.

348
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:25,560
Are there still people like that?

349
00:24:26,140 --> 00:24:28,779
At the very least... I know one person.

350
00:24:28,780 --> 00:24:30,413
There we go.

351
00:24:31,340 --> 00:24:34,019
- I understand now.
- What the hell?

352
00:24:34,019 --> 00:24:36,149
That damn happiness that you mentioned...

353
00:24:36,150 --> 00:24:40,639
Well, it's not because of the village. It's not because of the profession of being a teacher, Dude.

354
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:43,100
It's because of that person, man!

355
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,879
Here he is.

356
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,960
Speaking of the devil.

357
00:24:56,770 --> 00:25:02,109
Chang Yod was telling me that you were being cranky with him all day, Dude?

358
00:25:03,010 --> 00:25:05,089
Ai Mor. When did you arrive?

359
00:25:05,090 --> 00:25:07,009
Wow. Look.

360
00:25:07,010 --> 00:25:09,019
We have finished many bottles.

361
00:25:09,020 --> 00:25:10,879
Here, Chief.

362
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:15,150
I think that a gulp or two gulps would be good.

363
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:18,640
This helps you relax.

364
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,723
Ai Mor.

365
00:25:20,723 --> 00:25:23,489
If you arrived a long time ago, then where did Nong Tian go?

366
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:25,123
Look.

367
00:25:25,870 --> 00:25:29,429
Just as he sees my face. Bam. He asks about Nong Tian instantly.

368
00:25:29,429 --> 00:25:30,639
Right away.

369
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:34,209
Just as he sees my face, B-b-b-bam. I-i-instantly, he asks about Nong Tian.

370
00:25:34,209 --> 00:25:36,540
B-b-b-bam. I-i-instantly.

371
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:42,170
Nong Tian didn't come with me.

372
00:25:42,170 --> 00:25:44,879
His friend came to see him in the city center.

373
00:25:44,879 --> 00:25:47,339
So he's going to come back tomorrow instead.

374
00:25:47,339 --> 00:25:48,729
Who gave him permission?

375
00:25:48,730 --> 00:25:53,119
There he goes again. It's all about permission and permission,

376
00:25:53,119 --> 00:25:57,990
nothing but that all day, all night.

377
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:04,100
Alright, alright, alright. Drink some alcohol instead.

378
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,619
No need to be cranky, friend!

379
00:26:05,620 --> 00:26:07,089
Come on.

380
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:08,609
Hey, I'm not frustrated with you, Dude.

381
00:26:08,610 --> 00:26:10,339
I just want to knock some sense into you is all.

382
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:12,659
Yeah. Thanks, Dude.

383
00:26:12,660 --> 00:26:16,330
And so? This happiness of yours... who is it?

384
00:26:28,980 --> 00:26:33,113
Ai Tul... How would you feel

385
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:36,310
if I told you that...

386
00:26:36,310 --> 00:26:38,313
I like men?

387
00:26:39,410 --> 00:26:40,669
That's your business, of course.

388
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,559
Woah! That's it?

389
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:45,779
Huh? So how did you expect me to feel?

390
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:48,339
I thought that you might be... more shocked than this.

391
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:51,479
- So if I told you that I liked women, would you be shocked?
- Well, no.

392
00:26:51,479 --> 00:26:53,919
Yeah, so why the hell do I need to be shocked?

393
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,919
When it's just you getting to know yourself better.

394
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,569
Which I think... that's pretty ok though.

395
00:26:58,570 --> 00:27:00,169
Dude, but it's not the same at all.

396
00:27:00,170 --> 00:27:02,079
How, how is it not the same?

397
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:04,259
It's just like you like liking dogs while I like cats.

398
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:07,809
It's still just a preference though. Isn't that right?

399
00:27:07,809 --> 00:27:09,749
They're totally different matters, Dude.

400
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:11,819
Wait. Hold up.

401
00:27:11,820 --> 00:27:15,949
So then the person who's making your heart flutter and not want to go home...

402
00:27:15,950 --> 00:27:16,940
It's a guy?

403
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:25,159
But it's pretty strange, right? That Ai Nong Tian could stay here this long.

404
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:29,370
He'll be going back home soon.

405
00:27:30,650 --> 00:27:34,120
He'll be dearly missed then.

406
00:27:35,430 --> 00:27:38,369
Besides Khru Torfun,

407
00:27:38,370 --> 00:27:43,109
it's this teacher... that's suitable for...

408
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:48,410
Pha Pun Dao village.

409
00:27:49,580 --> 00:27:50,849
Ai Chang, well said!

410
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:52,899
Of course! I'm good at talking!

411
00:27:52,900 --> 00:27:54,999
I can say it right now that...

412
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:57,779
Just about everyone adores him.

413
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:01,700
Even myself, I also like him.

414
00:28:02,470 --> 00:28:05,359
What about you, Mor? Mor do you like him?

415
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,779
- Khru Tian?
- I like him.

416
00:28:08,990 --> 00:28:11,259
Ai Rang! And you, do you like him?

417
00:28:11,260 --> 00:28:13,110
I like him. I like him.

418
00:28:13,130 --> 00:28:14,559
What about you, Dude?

419
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:16,319
Do you like him?

420
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:19,429
I might just be feeling good with him is all, Dude.

421
00:28:19,430 --> 00:28:21,159
The feelings that I have for him

422
00:28:21,159 --> 00:28:23,789
I don't even know if it started from myself,

423
00:28:23,789 --> 00:28:29,169
or if it started because of Torfun, or...could it be because I'm gay?

424
00:28:29,169 --> 00:28:31,029
Are you crazy? Feelings,

425
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:34,649
they're born from your own brain, man. Not from someone else's heart.

426
00:28:35,450 --> 00:28:37,029
Ugh! I don't know anymore!

427
00:28:37,030 --> 00:28:38,639
Damn it.

428
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:41,519
The thing is, you need to separate them into different matters, Dude.

429
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,969
The matter of whether you're gay or not is one matter.

430
00:28:43,970 --> 00:28:46,179
And the matter of if you like him or not is another matter, Dude.

431
00:28:46,179 --> 00:28:47,649
Ai Tul! They're the same matter.

432
00:28:47,649 --> 00:28:50,959
If it's the same matter, then that means that you're gay and that you like him!

433
00:28:50,959 --> 00:28:52,869
You like men, then that means you're gay.

434
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:55,789
But I'm okay with it, Dude. Because you're my friend.

435
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:57,223
That's that.

436
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:02,233
Hey!

437
00:29:02,233 --> 00:29:04,469
And when did I tell you that I liked him?

438
00:29:04,469 --> 00:29:07,339
I saw the signs from you ever since the first day he came here.

439
00:29:07,340 --> 00:29:11,169
