492
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:17,130
I understand you.

493
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:21,630
Thanks, man.

494
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:26,439
And then I'll go and tell Ai Mark, Ai Lin, and Ai Ood. All of them.

495
00:33:26,439 --> 00:33:28,179
Ai Tul, you shit. You really...

496
00:33:28,179 --> 00:33:30,040
Just go back. Go.

497
00:33:31,750 --> 00:33:33,419
Oh, dude...

498
00:33:33,419 --> 00:33:37,240
And about Torfun,

499
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:40,600
I think that you should find a way to tell him.

500
00:33:41,250 --> 00:33:43,290
Trust me.

501
00:33:43,290 --> 00:33:45,580
Before it's too late.

502
00:33:48,170 --> 00:33:49,603
Yeah.

503
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:52,710
Before I go back,

504
00:33:52,710 --> 00:33:55,590
Let me get a selfie with you, just one picture, friend.

505
00:33:55,590 --> 00:33:57,123
Come here.

506
00:34:01,130 --> 00:34:03,929
Hey, Ai Tul. Don't be nosey and post it, Dude.

507
00:34:03,929 --> 00:34:05,920
Yeah, I know already.

508
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:08,479
I'm leaving then. If the friends ask,

509
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:12,100
I'll just tell them that you're stuck to a guy.

510
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:13,790
Ai Tul.

511
00:34:13,790 --> 00:34:15,490
(Piss off.)

512
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:48,330
Huh, Chief?

513
00:34:49,110 --> 00:34:51,860
Why? I can't come pick you up?

514
00:35:18,740 --> 00:35:20,659
Okay, Chief.

515
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:23,149
From now on, if I'm going to go somewhere,

516
00:35:23,150 --> 00:35:25,169
I'll inform you every time, Chief.

517
00:35:25,169 --> 00:35:26,603
Okay?

518
00:35:28,300 --> 00:35:30,233
What are you even saying?

519
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:33,080
Geez, well it's because you're being this quiet, Chief.

520
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,230
Chief, just go ahead and lecture me.

521
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:42,660
Where have you been?

522
00:35:43,790 --> 00:35:46,800
Well, my friend came on a trip to see me, like pretty suddenly.

523
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:49,300
I just wanted to go hang out with my friend for a day.

524
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:51,039
Next time...

525
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:54,399
It's you! Try to talk nicely to him sometimes.

526
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:58,000
You only ever make a stern face and always speak with an authoritative tone.

527
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:03,700
Next time...you can just invite your friend to come up and visit up here.

528
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:06,040
So where has your friend gone now?

529
00:36:07,470 --> 00:36:09,990
My friend went back home already.

530
00:36:13,740 --> 00:36:16,770
So...have you eaten anything yet?

531
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:22,399
O-Oh...Not yet. Not yet.

532
00:36:22,399 --> 00:36:24,490
I'm not really hungry yet.

533
00:36:26,180 --> 00:36:30,390
You! You should learn to be considerate of others sometimes.

534
00:36:30,390 --> 00:36:32,929
Nong Tian came up here to teach in the hills.

535
00:36:32,930 --> 00:36:35,379
Once he's done teaching, he just goes home.

536
00:36:35,380 --> 00:36:38,110
Did you know that he might want to go around to see things too?

537
00:36:50,690 --> 00:36:52,290
Hey, Chief.

538
00:36:52,290 --> 00:36:55,290
This is not the way back to Pha Pun Dao village.

539
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:57,839
I'm going to take you on a trip.

540
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,373
Huh?

541
00:37:00,690 --> 00:37:03,390
Chief, YOU taking me on a trip?

542
00:37:03,390 --> 00:37:05,130
Or do you not want to go?

543
00:37:06,670 --> 00:37:08,970
I'll go. I'll go. I'll go. Let's go.

544
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,573
Wow.

545
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:51,950
It's so damn beautiful, Chief.

546
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:56,250
This weather is so nice.

547
00:38:00,490 --> 00:38:02,010
Here.

548
00:38:02,010 --> 00:38:04,020
Eat this as a snack for now.

549
00:38:12,060 --> 00:38:14,020
Thank you, Chief.

550
00:38:24,100 --> 00:38:26,100
So, Chief, you're not going to eat any?

551
00:38:33,220 --> 00:38:34,529
Here.

552
00:38:34,530 --> 00:38:36,163
Let's share.

553
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:40,160
Come on.

554
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:43,450
No one else is around. You don't need to act cool.

555
00:38:57,220 --> 00:38:59,029
Here, eat it all.

556
00:38:59,030 --> 00:39:00,730
You just go ahead and eat it.

557
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:18,913
Chief.

558
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:25,079
Hey, Chief.

559
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:28,939
Do ever have any other expressions, other than the stuck-up one you make at me?

560
00:39:31,730 --> 00:39:34,480
My face is just like this to everyone.

561
00:39:36,740 --> 00:39:39,140
Do you have to make a stern face all the time?

562
00:39:40,830 --> 00:39:42,669
I'm a supervisor.

563
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:46,449
If I smile too much, what subordinates would take me seriously?

564
00:39:46,449 --> 00:39:49,690
But right now, there aren't any subordinates around though.

565
00:39:49,690 --> 00:39:52,180
Can you not be a chief for a moment?

566
00:39:52,980 --> 00:39:54,880
So what do you want me to be?

567
00:39:57,600 --> 00:39:59,580
To be a Phi, maybe?

568
00:40:02,580 --> 00:40:04,380
So call me Phi then.

569
00:40:05,290 --> 00:40:06,923
P'Phu.

570
00:40:08,520 --> 00:40:11,000
No. It's cringe.

571
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:14,599
Oh, Chief.

572
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:18,639
So...when you're happy, what kind of face do you make?

573
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:20,673
Can you show me?

574
00:40:20,673 --> 00:40:22,333
I smile like this, of course.

575
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:28,209
Then...when you smile for someone you like, such as smiling for a lover...

576
00:40:28,209 --> 00:40:30,020
Do you not know how to smile?

577
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,460
No wonder why you don't have a lover.

578
00:41:17,810 --> 00:41:20,060
There it is! A smile like that!

579
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:23,450
How come you know how to smile like that now?

580
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,690
What picture are you looking at?

581
00:41:31,390 --> 00:41:33,123
Let me take a look too.

582
00:41:34,900 --> 00:41:36,560
Let me see.

583
00:41:37,033 --> 00:41:38,589
Wow, you're just going to put it away?

584
00:41:38,590 --> 00:41:39,920
Fine, I won't look at it.

585
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,670
I'll go somewhere else then.

586
00:42:24,670 --> 00:42:26,370
I'll...

587
00:42:26,370 --> 00:42:28,240
go inside the house first then, alright?

588
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,193
Yeah.

589
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:46,693
Tian.

590
00:42:49,440 --> 00:42:50,873
Huh?

591
00:42:52,410 --> 00:42:56,619
Ai Phu, you're about 30 now!

592
00:42:56,619 --> 00:43:00,370
Make some moves. Don't just sit on the fence.

593
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:07,483
No.

594
00:43:08,020 --> 00:43:09,653
It's nothing.

595
00:43:14,790 --> 00:43:16,623
I'll get going then, alright?

596
00:43:23,050 --> 00:43:25,819
Dude, if you're not sure about how he feels about you,

597
00:43:25,820 --> 00:43:27,920
just make the first move on him.

598
00:43:28,950 --> 00:43:31,999
We are young. We are bold.

599
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:34,400
Go for it. Don't waste time.

600
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:54,393
Chief.

601
00:43:55,790 --> 00:43:57,223
Huh?

602
00:43:57,880 --> 00:44:01,270
Tomorrow...want to go fly kites together?

603
00:44:03,330 --> 00:44:04,863
Kites?

604
00:44:08,050 --> 00:44:12,720
What I mean is, tomorrow, I'm going to teach the kids to make a kite.

605
00:44:15,070 --> 00:44:18,639
If you're free...then come do it together.

606
00:44:20,320 --> 00:44:22,153
"Do it together"?

607
00:44:23,550 --> 00:44:27,840
I mean, tomorrow, come and create a kite together.

608
00:44:32,290 --> 00:44:33,723
Okay.

609
00:45:08,810 --> 00:45:10,750
You should go back now.

610
00:45:12,380 --> 00:45:14,550
You should go inside the house already too.

611
00:45:42,610 --> 00:45:44,029
Are you cold, everyone?

612
00:45:44,030 --> 00:45:46,069
Yes.

613
00:45:46,070 --> 00:45:48,670
Make sure you clean everything thoroughly.

614
00:45:49,930 --> 00:45:52,340
- Are you okay, Aai?
- I'm alright, I'm alright.

615
00:45:52,340 --> 00:45:56,020
When I went into the woods just now, there were so many snakes.

616
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:58,733
You need to look around carefully, alright?

617
00:45:59,230 --> 00:46:00,810
We're here.

618
00:46:01,990 --> 00:46:03,579
- Ayi.
- Yes?

619
00:46:03,580 --> 00:46:05,290
Come here.

620
00:46:05,290 --> 00:46:07,189
Are you not sweeping properly, huh?

621
00:46:07,190 --> 00:46:08,809
- Are you not sweeping properly?
- I am.

622
00:46:08,810 --> 00:46:10,500
Look at him.

623
00:46:10,500 --> 00:46:13,269
At first, I thought he wouldn't last more than 3 days for sure.

624
00:46:13,270 --> 00:46:16,510
And I'd have to drive him back to the bus terminal for sure.

625
00:46:16,510 --> 00:46:18,550
But look at him now.

626
00:46:19,550 --> 00:46:22,000
He seems like one of the people here.

627
00:46:26,660 --> 00:46:33,180
When I think about it, I feel sad. That soon, Khru, will have to return to Bangkok already.

628
00:46:33,180 --> 00:46:37,300
My true feelings are that I'd like him to stay here longer.

629
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:40,890
Chief, can't you help talk to Khru Tian?

630
00:46:44,290 --> 00:46:46,390
I can't, Chang.

631
00:46:46,390 --> 00:46:48,910
He still has a future ahead.

632
00:46:48,910 --> 00:46:50,860
He hasn't even finished school yet.

633
00:46:55,790 --> 00:46:57,623
What a shame, right?

634
00:46:58,470 --> 00:47:00,310
The kiddos...

635
00:47:02,110 --> 00:47:03,940
They love Khru already.

636
00:47:05,940 --> 00:47:08,140
Oh, Chief!

637
00:47:21,420 --> 00:47:24,540
So...what did you bring the bamboo for, Phi?

638
00:47:25,220 --> 00:47:26,910
Come on, come on. Let's put it away.

639
00:47:26,910 --> 00:47:29,370
We overheard that you'd be teaching how to make kites, Khru.

640
00:47:29,370 --> 00:47:35,009
- So we cut this bamboo for you to teach the kids to build kites.
- Come on, come on. Put it away.

641
00:47:35,010 --> 00:47:37,899
Yeah, that's true. I completely forgot about it.

642
00:47:37,900 --> 00:47:39,099
Give it over here, P' Rang. I'll help.

643
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,899
Oh, no need. No need.

644
00:47:40,899 --> 00:47:43,290
- Oh, it's alright, Phi.
- Alright, alright, alright.

645
00:47:43,290 --> 00:47:45,470
-Thank you for bringing these for me.
-Sure.

646
00:47:45,470 --> 00:47:47,039
I don't even know how to start yet.

647
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:49,659
We will cut them into small sticks for you.

648
00:47:49,660 --> 00:47:51,250
- Chang, you're going to cut them for us, right?
- That's right, that's right.

649
00:47:51,250 --> 00:47:53,210
Thank you so much.

650
00:47:54,290 --> 00:47:56,223
All done.

651
00:47:56,223 --> 00:48:01,069
Everyone! Today, I'll be teaching you all how to make kites!

652
00:48:01,069 --> 00:48:03,049
What is a kite?

653
00:48:03,049 --> 00:48:04,729
A kite?

654
00:48:04,730 --> 00:48:06,599
A kite is...

655
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:08,033
Well...

656
00:48:10,130 --> 00:48:12,510
It's a tiny big bird, of course!

657
00:48:14,350 --> 00:48:15,919
Alright, alright. No need to be confused, everyone.

658
00:48:15,920 --> 00:48:18,190
Let's just get right into making it. Come on.

659
00:48:18,730 --> 00:48:22,479
Here. Everyone, grab a stick for the frame.

660
00:48:22,479 --> 00:48:24,909
One each. Come on. One each.

661
00:48:24,910 --> 00:48:28,639
And then...have you picked a paper yet? Have you picked a colored paper for the kite yet?

662
00:48:30,370 --> 00:48:32,009
Apply the glue thinly.

663
00:48:32,009 --> 00:48:35,609
If you put it on too thick, the kite won't be able to fly.

664
00:48:35,610 --> 00:48:37,730
A plane can go up though.

665
00:48:37,730 --> 00:48:40,849
It's not the same though, right? Here, take a look here.

666
00:48:42,040 --> 00:48:47,339
A plane, alright, has wings that help it to be able to be lifted in the air.

667
00:48:47,340 --> 00:48:49,150
With the principle that

668
00:48:49,150 --> 00:48:52,279
it allows the air to flow over towards the end of the wings at high speed.

669
00:48:52,280 --> 00:48:56,110
It makes it generates enough force to make the plane

670
00:48:56,110 --> 00:48:59,300
be able to float up, just like this.

671
00:49:04,690 --> 00:49:06,390
What are you smiling at?

672
00:49:07,220 --> 00:49:10,270
When you were talking, you looked pretty happy.

673
00:49:16,190 --> 00:49:18,340
[Pha Pun Dao School]

674
00:49:22,870 --> 00:49:25,020
What are you doing?

675
00:49:25,020 --> 00:49:28,239
This one is called a Pak Pao kite.

676
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:30,773
Huh?

677
00:49:30,773 --> 00:49:33,279
If you knew how to make a kite, why didn't you say so?

678
00:49:33,280 --> 00:49:35,880
If I know how to do it, do I have to tell others too?

679
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:41,410
Hey, Chief.

680
00:49:41,410 --> 00:49:42,849
I'm not being dirty.
[T/N: The literal phrase for flying a kite is "to tug/pull a kite"; It's also a known sexual innuendo]

681
00:49:42,849 --> 00:49:45,089
Well, you've never asked me about kites though.

682
00:49:45,089 --> 00:49:47,009
I'm a rural boy.

683
00:49:47,010 --> 00:49:49,410
What does being rural have anything to do with it?

684
00:49:51,410 --> 00:49:55,230
Well, I didn't have remote control cars. I didn't have games to press and play.

685
00:49:55,910 --> 00:49:58,660
So just this kite was already amazing.

686
00:50:00,830 --> 00:50:03,579
How is it? Does it look good?

687
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,780
It's pretty awesome.

688
00:50:07,350 --> 00:50:09,250
Make one for me.

689
00:50:12,810 --> 00:50:16,520
I want one like this. Can I have it?

690
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:18,249
You can't, Ayi.

691
00:50:18,249 --> 00:50:22,040
This one... has an owner already.

692
00:50:22,990 --> 00:50:25,140
He can't even give a kid one, huh?

693
00:50:26,870 --> 00:50:30,160
Let's go. Let's go play with our kites outside instead, alright?

694
00:50:32,330 --> 00:50:36,269
Alright, everyone! It's time to take our big birds out to fly now.

695
00:50:36,269 --> 00:50:39,199
- Are you ready?
- We're ready!

696
00:50:39,199 --> 00:50:42,130
- Yay! Come on, let's go!
- Yay!

697
00:50:43,030 --> 00:50:45,430
[For Khru Seetian]

698
00:51:03,890 --> 00:51:06,150
Alright, everyone. Hurry up and follow me.

699
00:51:09,350 --> 00:51:11,669
Hey, Longtae!

700
00:51:11,670 --> 00:51:13,129
Oh, P' Tian!

701
00:51:13,130 --> 00:51:15,269
- Are you here to take photos for fun?
- That's right.

702
00:51:15,269 --> 00:51:18,099
- Are you free?
- What's up, Phi? I'm free, Phi. What's up?

703
00:51:18,099 --> 00:51:19,759
Can you help the kids with their kites?

704
00:51:19,760 --> 00:51:21,810
Sure, Phi.

705
00:51:21,810 --> 00:51:24,550
Hi, Yod. Hi, Rang.

706
00:51:24,550 --> 00:51:27,180
Hey! Come on, come on.

707
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:36,190
Chief Phu?

708
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,449
What do you want?

709
00:51:38,450 --> 00:51:40,850
Calling me by my full title like that...

710
00:51:43,580 --> 00:51:45,580
How do you fly a kite?

711
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:10,013
Everyone, gather right here.

712
00:52:10,013 --> 00:52:13,020
Come, come, come.

713
00:52:13,020 --> 00:52:14,920
We're going to get in pairs, alright?

714
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:16,799
One person holds the rope.

715
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:18,759
And the other person will send the kite to the sky.

716
00:52:18,760 --> 00:52:20,760
Once we count one, two, three...

717
00:52:20,760 --> 00:52:23,339
The person holding the rope will run this way.

718
00:52:23,340 --> 00:52:26,189
while the person with the kite pushes it up in the opposite direction of the wind.

719
00:52:26,190 --> 00:52:28,060
Understood?

720
00:52:28,060 --> 00:52:29,980
- Do you guys understand?
- Yes, Sir.

721
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:32,230
Go on, kids. Let's try it out.

722
00:52:32,230 --> 00:52:34,940
Let's go! Let's do it! Let's do it!

723
00:53:55,790 --> 00:53:57,323
Tian!

724
00:53:58,430 --> 00:53:59,850
Tian!

725
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:01,640
P'Tian!

726
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:04,320
Aai Seetian!

727
00:54:06,980 --> 00:54:09,749
Tian! Tian!

728
00:54:09,749 --> 00:54:11,850
Tian! Tian! Tian!

729
00:54:15,230 --> 00:54:16,863
Tian!

730
00:54:24,230 --> 00:54:26,063
Ai Mor!

731
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:46,710
[Directed by Noppharnach Chaiwimol]

732
00:54:56,740 --> 00:54:59,660
I thought you would've taken me to see the scenic landscape.

733
00:54:59,660 --> 00:55:00,949
I'm sleepy.

734
00:55:00,950 --> 00:55:03,100
So I was looking for something to drink to combat my sleepiness.

735
00:55:03,100 --> 00:55:05,000
Do you want one, too?

736
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:07,409
I want it. I want one cup.

737
00:55:07,409 --> 00:55:09,399
I'll make it for you. Go and have a seat first.

738
00:55:09,400 --> 00:55:13,459
Hey, hey, hey! Chief, you go sit. I'll make it for you.

739
00:55:13,460 --> 00:55:15,293
Move over.

740
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:21,000
You went out of your way to drive a long way to pick me up, no?

741
00:55:55,260 --> 00:55:56,893
Chief.

742
00:56:09,730 --> 00:56:11,463
How is it?

743
00:56:13,460 --> 00:56:15,060
It's good.

744
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:18,089
Chief, did you know?

745
00:56:18,090 --> 00:56:21,240
Chief, you're the first person I've made coffee for.

746
00:56:32,970 --> 00:56:35,949
It's a bit intense. Do you like it?

747
00:56:35,950 --> 00:56:38,990
Yeah, I tend to like it pretty intense.

748
00:56:40,890 --> 00:56:42,810
I'm also intense.

749
00:56:47,280 --> 00:56:49,429
I meant the coffee though.

750
00:56:49,430 --> 00:56:51,279
I also meant the coffee.

751
00:56:51,280 --> 00:56:53,180
What are YOU thinking of?

752
00:57:13,570 --> 00:57:18,500
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

753
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:24,060
♫ Stop right there, that's enough. Understand? ♫

754
00:57:24,060 --> 00:57:29,640
♫ I keep repeatedly telling my heart to stop dreaming ♫

755
00:57:29,640 --> 00:57:35,100
♫ When reality probably won't be like in fairytales ♫

756
00:57:35,100 --> 00:57:42,070
♫ Where it's you and me with a love that's beautiful ♫

757
00:57:42,070 --> 00:57:47,520
♫ I'm trying to bury it deep within my heart ♫

758
00:57:47,520 --> 00:57:50,290
♫ What should I do so that you won't know? ♫

759
00:57:50,290 --> 00:57:55,459
[Preview]
Heart surgery and a heart transplant surgery are completely different things though.

760
00:57:55,460 --> 00:57:59,360
And such a big matter like this... Why didn't you tell us, Phi?

761
00:57:59,360 --> 00:58:03,359
Ayi told me the villagers hadn't harvested tea leaves for several weeks.

762
00:58:03,360 --> 00:58:06,009
